59std::unique_ptr<NetEqController> CreateNetEqController(
60 const NetEqControllerFactory& controller_factory,
61 int base_min_delay,
62 int max_packets_in_buffer,
63 bool enable_rtx_handling,
64 bool allow_time_stretching,
65 TickTimer* tick_timer,
66 webrtc::Clock* clock) {
67 NetEqController::Config config;
68 config.base_min_delay_ms = base_min_delay;
69 config.max_packets_in_buffer = max_packets_in_buffer;
70 config.enable_rtx_handling = enable_rtx_handling;
71 config.allow_time_stretching = allow_time_stretching;
72 config.tick_timer = tick_timer;
73 config.clock = clock;
74 return controller_factory.CreateNetEqController(config);
75}
76
77int GetDelayChainLengthMs(int config_extra_delay_ms) {
78 constexpr char kExtraDelayFieldTrial[] = "WebRTC-Audio-NetEqExtraDelay";
79 if (webrtc::field_trial::IsEnabled(kExtraDelayFieldTrial)) {
80 const auto field_trial_string =
81 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kExtraDelayFieldTrial);
82 int extra_delay_ms = -1;
83 if (sscanf(field_trial_string.c_str(), "Enabled-%d", &extra_delay_ms) ==
84 1 &&
85 extra_delay_ms >= 0 && extra_delay_ms <= 2000) {
86 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Delay chain length set to " << extra_delay_ms
87 << " ms in field trial";
88 return (extra_delay_ms / 10) * 10; // Rounding down to multiple of 10.
89 }
90 }
91 // Field trial not set, or invalid value read. Use value from config.
92 return config_extra_delay_ms;
93}

97NetEqImpl::Dependencies::Dependencies(
98 const NetEq::Config& config,
99 Clock* clock,
100 const rtc::scoped_refptr<AudioDecoderFactory>& decoder_factory,
101 const NetEqControllerFactory& controller_factory)
102 : clock(clock),
103 tick_timer(new TickTimer),
104 stats(new StatisticsCalculator),
105 decoder_database(
106 new DecoderDatabase(decoder_factory, config.codec_pair_id)),
107 dtmf_buffer(new DtmfBuffer(config.sample_rate_hz)),
108 dtmf_tone_generator(new DtmfToneGenerator),
109 packet_buffer(
110 new PacketBuffer(config.max_packets_in_buffer, tick_timer.get())),
111 neteq_controller(
112 CreateNetEqController(controller_factory,
113 config.min_delay_ms,
114 config.max_packets_in_buffer,
115 config.enable_rtx_handling,
116 !config.for_test_no_time_stretching,
117 tick_timer.get(),
118 clock)),
119 red_payload_splitter(new RedPayloadSplitter),
120 timestamp_scaler(new TimestampScaler(*decoder_database)),
121 accelerate_factory(new AccelerateFactory),
122 expand_factory(new ExpandFactory),
123 preemptive_expand_factory(new PreemptiveExpandFactory) {}
124
125NetEqImpl::Dependencies::~Dependencies() = default;

127NetEqImpl::NetEqImpl(const NetEq::Config& config,
128 Dependencies&& deps,
129 bool create_components)
130 : clock_(deps.clock),
131 tick_timer_(std::move(deps.tick_timer)),
132 decoder_database_(std::move(deps.decoder_database)),
133 dtmf_buffer_(std::move(deps.dtmf_buffer)),
134 dtmf_tone_generator_(std::move(deps.dtmf_tone_generator)),
135 packet_buffer_(std::move(deps.packet_buffer)),
136 red_payload_splitter_(std::move(deps.red_payload_splitter)),
137 timestamp_scaler_(std::move(deps.timestamp_scaler)),
138 vad_(new PostDecodeVad()),
139 expand_factory_(std::move(deps.expand_factory)),
140 accelerate_factory_(std::move(deps.accelerate_factory)),
141 preemptive_expand_factory_(std::move(deps.preemptive_expand_factory)),
142 stats_(std::move(deps.stats)),
143 controller_(std::move(deps.neteq_controller)),
144 last_mode_(Mode::kNormal),
145 decoded_buffer_length_(kMaxFrameSize),
146 decoded_buffer_(new int16_t[decoded_buffer_length_]),
147 playout_timestamp_(0),
148 new_codec_(false),
149 timestamp_(0),
150 reset_decoder_(false),
151 first_packet_(true),
152 enable_fast_accelerate_(config.enable_fast_accelerate),
153 nack_enabled_(false),
154 enable_muted_state_(config.enable_muted_state),
155 expand_uma_logger_("WebRTC.Audio.ExpandRatePercent",
156 10, // Report once every 10 s.
157 tick_timer_.get()),
158 speech_expand_uma_logger_("WebRTC.Audio.SpeechExpandRatePercent",
159 10, // Report once every 10 s.
160 tick_timer_.get()),
161 no_time_stretching_(config.for_test_no_time_stretching),
162 enable_rtx_handling_(config.enable_rtx_handling),
163 output_delay_chain_ms_(
164 GetDelayChainLengthMs(config.extra_output_delay_ms)),
165 output_delay_chain_(rtc::CheckedDivExact(output_delay_chain_ms_, 10)) {
166 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "NetEq config: " << config.ToString();
167 int fs = config.sample_rate_hz;
168 if (fs != 8000 && fs != 16000 && fs != 32000 && fs != 48000) {
169 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Sample rate " << fs
170 << " Hz not supported. "
171 "Changing to 8000 Hz.";
172 fs = 8000;
173 }
174 controller_->SetMaximumDelay(config.max_delay_ms);
175 fs_hz_ = fs;
176 fs_mult_ = fs / 8000;
177 last_output_sample_rate_hz_ = fs;
178 output_size_samples_ = static_cast<size_t>(kOutputSizeMs * 8 * fs_mult_);
179 controller_->SetSampleRate(fs_hz_, output_size_samples_);
180 decoder_frame_length_ = 2 * output_size_samples_; // 20 ms.
181 if (create_components) {
182 SetSampleRateAndChannels(fs, 1); // Default is 1 channel.
183 }
184 RTC_DCHECK(!vad_->enabled());
185 if (config.enable_post_decode_vad) {
186 vad_->Enable();
187 }
188}

192int NetEqImpl::InsertPacket(const RTPHeader& rtp_header,
193 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload) {
194 rtc::MsanCheckInitialized(payload);
195 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "NetEqImpl::InsertPacket");
196 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
197 if (InsertPacketInternal(rtp_header, payload) != 0) {
198 return kFail;
199 }
200 return kOK;
201}

205 // rtp_header parameter.

207 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
208 controller_->RegisterEmptyPacket();
209}

211namespace {
212void SetAudioFrameActivityAndType(bool vad_enabled,
213 NetEqImpl::OutputType type,
214 AudioFrame::VADActivity last_vad_activity,
215 AudioFrame* audio_frame) {
216 switch (type) {
217 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kNormalSpeech: {
218 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kNormalSpeech;
219 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = AudioFrame::kVadActive;
220 break;
221 }
222 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kVadPassive: {
223 // This should only be reached if the VAD is enabled.
224 RTC_DCHECK(vad_enabled);
225 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kNormalSpeech;
226 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = AudioFrame::kVadPassive;
227 break;
228 }
229 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kCNG: {
230 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kCNG;
231 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = AudioFrame::kVadPassive;
232 break;
233 }
234 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kPLC: {
235 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kPLC;
236 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = last_vad_activity;
237 break;
238 }
239 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kPLCCNG: {
240 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kPLCCNG;
241 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = AudioFrame::kVadPassive;
242 break;
243 }
244 case NetEqImpl::OutputType::kCodecPLC: {
245 audio_frame->speech_type_ = AudioFrame::kCodecPLC;
246 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = last_vad_activity;
247 break;
248 }
249 default:
250 RTC_NOTREACHED();
251 }
252 if (!vad_enabled) {
253 // Always set kVadUnknown when receive VAD is inactive.
254 audio_frame->vad_activity_ = AudioFrame::kVadUnknown;
255 }
256}

259int NetEqImpl::GetAudio(AudioFrame* audio_frame,
260 bool* muted,
261 absl::optional<Operation> action_override) {
262 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "NetEqImpl::GetAudio");
263 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
264 if (GetAudioInternal(audio_frame, muted, action_override) != 0) {
265 return kFail;
266 }
267 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(
268 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_,
269 rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(audio_frame->samples_per_channel_ * 100));
270 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(*muted, audio_frame->muted());
271 SetAudioFrameActivityAndType(vad_->enabled(), LastOutputType(),
272 last_vad_activity_, audio_frame);
273 last_vad_activity_ = audio_frame->vad_activity_;
274 last_output_sample_rate_hz_ = audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_;
275 RTC_DCHECK(last_output_sample_rate_hz_ == 8000 ||
276 last_output_sample_rate_hz_ == 16000 ||
277 last_output_sample_rate_hz_ == 32000 ||
278 last_output_sample_rate_hz_ == 48000)
279 << "Unexpected sample rate " << last_output_sample_rate_hz_;
280
281 if (!output_delay_chain_.empty()) {
282 if (output_delay_chain_empty_) {
283 for (auto& f : output_delay_chain_) {
284 f.CopyFrom(*audio_frame);
285 }
286 output_delay_chain_empty_ = false;
287 delayed_last_output_sample_rate_hz_ = last_output_sample_rate_hz_;
288 } else {
289 RTC_DCHECK_GE(output_delay_chain_ix_, 0);
290 RTC_DCHECK_LT(output_delay_chain_ix_, output_delay_chain_.size());
291 swap(output_delay_chain_[output_delay_chain_ix_], *audio_frame);
292 *muted = audio_frame->muted();
293 output_delay_chain_ix_ =
294 (output_delay_chain_ix_ + 1) % output_delay_chain_.size();
295 delayed_last_output_sample_rate_hz_ = audio_frame->sample_rate_hz();
296 }
297 }
298
299 return kOK;
300}

302void NetEqImpl::SetCodecs(const std::map<int, SdpAudioFormat>& codecs) {
303 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
304 const std::vector<int> changed_payload_types =
305 decoder_database_->SetCodecs(codecs);
306 for (const int pt : changed_payload_types) {
307 packet_buffer_->DiscardPacketsWithPayloadType(pt, stats_.get());
308 }
309}

311bool NetEqImpl::RegisterPayloadType(int rtp_payload_type,
312 const SdpAudioFormat& audio_format) {
313 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "NetEqImpl::RegisterPayloadType: payload type "
314 << rtp_payload_type << ", codec "
315 << rtc::ToString(audio_format);
316 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
317 return decoder_database_->RegisterPayload(rtp_payload_type, audio_format) ==
318 DecoderDatabase::kOK;
319}
320
321int NetEqImpl::RemovePayloadType(uint8_t rtp_payload_type) {
322 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
323 int ret = decoder_database_->Remove(rtp_payload_type);
324 if (ret == DecoderDatabase::kOK || ret == DecoderDatabase::kDecoderNotFound) {
325 packet_buffer_->DiscardPacketsWithPayloadType(rtp_payload_type,
326 stats_.get());
327 return kOK;
328 }
329 return kFail;
330}

338 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
339 if (delay_ms >= 0 && delay_ms <= 10000) {
340 assert(controller_.get());
341 return controller_->SetMinimumDelay(

375
376int NetEqImpl::FilteredCurrentDelayMs() const {
377 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
378 // Sum up the filtered packet buffer level with the future length of the sync
379 // buffer.
380 const int delay_samples =
381 controller_->GetFilteredBufferLevel() + sync_buffer_->FutureLength();
382 // The division below will truncate. The return value is in ms.
383 return delay_samples / rtc::CheckedDivExact(fs_hz_, 1000) +
384 output_delay_chain_ms_;
385}

387int NetEqImpl::NetworkStatistics(NetEqNetworkStatistics* stats) {
388 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
389 assert(decoder_database_.get());
390 *stats = CurrentNetworkStatisticsInternal();
391 stats_->GetNetworkStatistics(decoder_frame_length_, stats);
392 // Compensate for output delay chain.
393 stats->mean_waiting_time_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
394 stats->median_waiting_time_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
395 stats->min_waiting_time_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
396 stats->max_waiting_time_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
397 return 0;
398}

400NetEqNetworkStatistics NetEqImpl::CurrentNetworkStatistics() const {
401 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
402 return CurrentNetworkStatisticsInternal();
403}
404
405NetEqNetworkStatistics NetEqImpl::CurrentNetworkStatisticsInternal() const {
406 assert(decoder_database_.get());
407 NetEqNetworkStatistics stats;
408 const size_t total_samples_in_buffers =
409 packet_buffer_->NumSamplesInBuffer(decoder_frame_length_) +
410 sync_buffer_->FutureLength();
411
412 assert(controller_.get());
413 stats.preferred_buffer_size_ms = controller_->TargetLevelMs();
414 stats.jitter_peaks_found = controller_->PeakFound();
415 RTC_DCHECK_GT(fs_hz_, 0);
416 stats.current_buffer_size_ms =
417 static_cast<uint16_t>(total_samples_in_buffers * 1000 / fs_hz_);
418
419 // Compensate for output delay chain.
420 stats.current_buffer_size_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
421 stats.preferred_buffer_size_ms += output_delay_chain_ms_;
422 return stats;
423}

430NetEqOperationsAndState NetEqImpl::GetOperationsAndState() const {
431 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
432 auto result = stats_->GetOperationsAndState();
433 result.current_buffer_size_ms =
434 (packet_buffer_->NumSamplesInBuffer(decoder_frame_length_) +
435 sync_buffer_->FutureLength()) *
436 1000 / fs_hz_;
437 result.current_frame_size_ms = decoder_frame_length_ * 1000 / fs_hz_;
438 result.next_packet_available = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket() &&
439 packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket()->timestamp ==
440 sync_buffer_->end_timestamp();
441 return result;
442}

456absl::optional<uint32_t> NetEqImpl::GetPlayoutTimestamp() const {
457 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
458 if (first_packet_ || last_mode_ == Mode::kRfc3389Cng ||
459 last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecInternalCng) {
460 // We don't have a valid RTP timestamp until we have decoded our first
461 // RTP packet. Also, the RTP timestamp is not accurate while playing CNG,
462 // which is indicated by returning an empty value.
463 return absl::nullopt;
464 }
465 size_t sum_samples_in_output_delay_chain = 0;
466 for (const auto& audio_frame : output_delay_chain_) {
467 sum_samples_in_output_delay_chain += audio_frame.samples_per_channel();
468 }
469 return timestamp_scaler_->ToExternal(
470 playout_timestamp_ -
471 static_cast<uint32_t>(sum_samples_in_output_delay_chain));
472}

474int NetEqImpl::last_output_sample_rate_hz() const {
475 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
476 return delayed_last_output_sample_rate_hz_.value_or(
477 last_output_sample_rate_hz_);
478}

480absl::optional<NetEq::DecoderFormat> NetEqImpl::GetDecoderFormat(
481 int payload_type) const {
482 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
483 const DecoderDatabase::DecoderInfo* const di =
484 decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(payload_type);
485 if (di) {
486 const AudioDecoder* const decoder = di->GetDecoder();
487 // TODO(kwiberg): Why the special case for RED?
488 return DecoderFormat{
489 /*sample_rate_hz=*/di->IsRed() ? 8000 : di->SampleRateHz(),
490 /*num_channels=*/
491 decoder ? rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(decoder->Channels()) : 1,
492 /*sdp_format=*/di->GetFormat()};
493 } else {
494 // Payload type not registered.
495 return absl::nullopt;
496 }
497}

499void NetEqImpl::FlushBuffers() {
500 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
501 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "FlushBuffers";
502 packet_buffer_->Flush(stats_.get());
503 assert(sync_buffer_.get());
504 assert(expand_.get());
505 sync_buffer_->Flush();
506 sync_buffer_->set_next_index(sync_buffer_->next_index() -
507 expand_->overlap_length());
508 // Set to wait for new codec.
509 first_packet_ = true;
510}

512void NetEqImpl::EnableNack(size_t max_nack_list_size) {
513 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
514 if (!nack_enabled_) {
515 const int kNackThresholdPackets = 2;
516 nack_.reset(NackTracker::Create(kNackThresholdPackets));
517 nack_enabled_ = true;
518 nack_->UpdateSampleRate(fs_hz_);
519 }
520 nack_->SetMaxNackListSize(max_nack_list_size);
521}
522
523void NetEqImpl::DisableNack() {
524 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
525 nack_.reset();
526 nack_enabled_ = false;
527}

559// Methods below this line are private.
560
561int NetEqImpl::InsertPacketInternal(const RTPHeader& rtp_header,
562 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> payload) {
563 if (payload.empty()) {
564 RTC_LOG_F(LS_ERROR) << "payload is empty";
565 return kInvalidPointer;
566 }
567
568 Timestamp receive_time = clock_->CurrentTime();
569 stats_->ReceivedPacket();
570
571 PacketList packet_list;
572 // Insert packet in a packet list.
573 packet_list.push_back([&rtp_header, &payload, &receive_time] {
574 // Convert to Packet.
575 Packet packet;
576 packet.payload_type = rtp_header.payloadType;
577 packet.sequence_number = rtp_header.sequenceNumber;
578 packet.timestamp = rtp_header.timestamp;
579 packet.payload.SetData(payload.data(), payload.size());
580 packet.packet_info = RtpPacketInfo(rtp_header, receive_time);
581 // Waiting time will be set upon inserting the packet in the buffer.
582 RTC_DCHECK(!packet.waiting_time);
583 return packet;
584 }());
585
586 bool update_sample_rate_and_channels = first_packet_;
587
588 if (update_sample_rate_and_channels) {
589 // Reset timestamp scaling.
590 timestamp_scaler_->Reset();
591 }
592
593 if (!decoder_database_->IsRed(rtp_header.payloadType)) {
594 // Scale timestamp to internal domain (only for some codecs).
595 timestamp_scaler_->ToInternal(&packet_list);
596 }
597
598 // Store these for later use, since the first packet may very well disappear
599 // before we need these values.
600 uint32_t main_timestamp = packet_list.front().timestamp;
601 uint8_t main_payload_type = packet_list.front().payload_type;
602 uint16_t main_sequence_number = packet_list.front().sequence_number;
603
604 // Reinitialize NetEq if it's needed (changed SSRC or first call).
605 if (update_sample_rate_and_channels) {
606 // Note: |first_packet_| will be cleared further down in this method, once
607 // the packet has been successfully inserted into the packet buffer.
608
609 // Flush the packet buffer and DTMF buffer.
610 packet_buffer_->Flush(stats_.get());
611 dtmf_buffer_->Flush();
612
613 // Update audio buffer timestamp.
614 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(main_timestamp - timestamp_);
615
616 // Update codecs.
617 timestamp_ = main_timestamp;
618 }
619
620 if (nack_enabled_) {
621 RTC_DCHECK(nack_);
622 if (update_sample_rate_and_channels) {
623 nack_->Reset();
624 }
625 nack_->UpdateLastReceivedPacket(rtp_header.sequenceNumber,
626 rtp_header.timestamp);
627 }
628
629 // Check for RED payload type, and separate payloads into several packets.
630 if (decoder_database_->IsRed(rtp_header.payloadType)) {
631 if (!red_payload_splitter_->SplitRed(&packet_list)) {
632 return kRedundancySplitError;
633 }
634 // Only accept a few RED payloads of the same type as the main data,
635 // DTMF events and CNG.
636 red_payload_splitter_->CheckRedPayloads(&packet_list, *decoder_database_);
637 if (packet_list.empty()) {
638 return kRedundancySplitError;
639 }
640 }
641
642 // Check payload types.
643 if (decoder_database_->CheckPayloadTypes(packet_list) ==
644 DecoderDatabase::kDecoderNotFound) {
645 return kUnknownRtpPayloadType;
646 }
647
648 RTC_DCHECK(!packet_list.empty());
649
650 // Update main_timestamp, if new packets appear in the list
651 // after RED splitting.
652 if (decoder_database_->IsRed(rtp_header.payloadType)) {
653 timestamp_scaler_->ToInternal(&packet_list);
654 main_timestamp = packet_list.front().timestamp;
655 main_payload_type = packet_list.front().payload_type;
656 main_sequence_number = packet_list.front().sequence_number;
657 }
658
659 // Process DTMF payloads. Cycle through the list of packets, and pick out any
660 // DTMF payloads found.
661 PacketList::iterator it = packet_list.begin();
662 while (it != packet_list.end()) {
663 const Packet& current_packet = (*it);
664 RTC_DCHECK(!current_packet.payload.empty());
665 if (decoder_database_->IsDtmf(current_packet.payload_type)) {
666 DtmfEvent event;
667 int ret = DtmfBuffer::ParseEvent(current_packet.timestamp,
668 current_packet.payload.data(),
669 current_packet.payload.size(), &event);
670 if (ret != DtmfBuffer::kOK) {
671 return kDtmfParsingError;
672 }
673 if (dtmf_buffer_->InsertEvent(event) != DtmfBuffer::kOK) {
674 return kDtmfInsertError;
675 }
676 it = packet_list.erase(it);
677 } else {
678 ++it;
679 }
680 }
681
682 PacketList parsed_packet_list;
683 bool is_dtx = false;
684 while (!packet_list.empty()) {
685 Packet& packet = packet_list.front();
686 const DecoderDatabase::DecoderInfo* info =
687 decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(packet.payload_type);
688 if (!info) {
689 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "SplitAudio unknown payload type";
690 return kUnknownRtpPayloadType;
691 }
692
693 if (info->IsComfortNoise()) {
694 // Carry comfort noise packets along.
695 parsed_packet_list.splice(parsed_packet_list.end(), packet_list,
696 packet_list.begin());
697 } else {
698 const auto sequence_number = packet.sequence_number;
699 const auto payload_type = packet.payload_type;
700 const Packet::Priority original_priority = packet.priority;
701 const auto& packet_info = packet.packet_info;
702 auto packet_from_result = [&](AudioDecoder::ParseResult& result) {
703 Packet new_packet;
704 new_packet.sequence_number = sequence_number;
705 new_packet.payload_type = payload_type;
706 new_packet.timestamp = result.timestamp;
707 new_packet.priority.codec_level = result.priority;
708 new_packet.priority.red_level = original_priority.red_level;
709 new_packet.packet_info = packet_info;
710 new_packet.frame = std::move(result.frame);
711 return new_packet;
712 };
713
714 std::vector<AudioDecoder::ParseResult> results =
715 info->GetDecoder()->ParsePayload(std::move(packet.payload),
716 packet.timestamp);
717 if (results.empty()) {
718 packet_list.pop_front();
719 } else {
720 bool first = true;
721 for (auto& result : results) {
722 RTC_DCHECK(result.frame);
723 RTC_DCHECK_GE(result.priority, 0);
724 is_dtx = is_dtx || result.frame->IsDtxPacket();
725 if (first) {
726 // Re-use the node and move it to parsed_packet_list.
727 packet_list.front() = packet_from_result(result);
728 parsed_packet_list.splice(parsed_packet_list.end(), packet_list,
729 packet_list.begin());
730 first = false;
731 } else {
732 parsed_packet_list.push_back(packet_from_result(result));
733 }
734 }
735 }
736 }
737 }
738
739 // Calculate the number of primary (non-FEC/RED) packets.
740 const size_t number_of_primary_packets = std::count_if(
741 parsed_packet_list.begin(), parsed_packet_list.end(),
742 [](const Packet& in) { return in.priority.codec_level == 0; });
743 if (number_of_primary_packets < parsed_packet_list.size()) {
744 stats_->SecondaryPacketsReceived(parsed_packet_list.size() -
745 number_of_primary_packets);
746 }
747
748 // Insert packets in buffer.
749 const int target_level_ms = controller_->TargetLevelMs();
750 const int ret = packet_buffer_->InsertPacketList(
751 &parsed_packet_list, *decoder_database_, &current_rtp_payload_type_,
752 &current_cng_rtp_payload_type_, stats_.get(), decoder_frame_length_,
753 last_output_sample_rate_hz_, target_level_ms);
754 bool buffer_flush_occured = false;
755 if (ret == PacketBuffer::kFlushed) {
756 // Reset DSP timestamp etc. if packet buffer flushed.
757 new_codec_ = true;
758 update_sample_rate_and_channels = true;
759 buffer_flush_occured = true;
760 } else if (ret == PacketBuffer::kPartialFlush) {
761 // Forward sync buffer timestamp
762 timestamp_ = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket()->timestamp;
763 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(timestamp_ -
764 sync_buffer_->end_timestamp());
765 buffer_flush_occured = true;
766 } else if (ret != PacketBuffer::kOK) {
767 return kOtherError;
768 }
769
770 if (first_packet_) {
771 first_packet_ = false;
772 // Update the codec on the next GetAudio call.
773 new_codec_ = true;
774 }
775
776 if (current_rtp_payload_type_) {
777 RTC_DCHECK(decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(*current_rtp_payload_type_))
778 << "Payload type " << static_cast<int>(*current_rtp_payload_type_)
779 << " is unknown where it shouldn't be";
780 }
781
782 if (update_sample_rate_and_channels && !packet_buffer_->Empty()) {
783 // We do not use |current_rtp_payload_type_| to |set payload_type|, but
784 // get the next RTP header from |packet_buffer_| to obtain the payload type.
785 // The reason for it is the following corner case. If NetEq receives a
786 // CNG packet with a sample rate different than the current CNG then it
787 // flushes its buffer, assuming send codec must have been changed. However,
788 // payload type of the hypothetically new send codec is not known.
789 const Packet* next_packet = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket();
790 RTC_DCHECK(next_packet);
791 const int payload_type = next_packet->payload_type;
792 size_t channels = 1;
793 if (!decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(payload_type)) {
794 AudioDecoder* decoder = decoder_database_->GetDecoder(payload_type);
795 assert(decoder); // Payloads are already checked to be valid.
796 channels = decoder->Channels();
797 }
798 const DecoderDatabase::DecoderInfo* decoder_info =
799 decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(payload_type);
800 assert(decoder_info);
801 if (decoder_info->SampleRateHz() != fs_hz_ ||
802 channels != algorithm_buffer_->Channels()) {
803 SetSampleRateAndChannels(decoder_info->SampleRateHz(), channels);
804 }
805 if (nack_enabled_) {
806 RTC_DCHECK(nack_);
807 // Update the sample rate even if the rate is not new, because of Reset().
808 nack_->UpdateSampleRate(fs_hz_);
809 }
810 }
811
812 const DecoderDatabase::DecoderInfo* dec_info =
813 decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(main_payload_type);
814 assert(dec_info); // Already checked that the payload type is known.
815
816 NetEqController::PacketArrivedInfo info;
817 info.is_cng_or_dtmf = dec_info->IsComfortNoise() || dec_info->IsDtmf();
818 info.packet_length_samples =
819 number_of_primary_packets * decoder_frame_length_;
820 info.main_timestamp = main_timestamp;
821 info.main_sequence_number = main_sequence_number;
822 info.is_dtx = is_dtx;
823 info.buffer_flush = buffer_flush_occured;
824 // Only update statistics if incoming packet is not older than last played
825 // out packet or RTX handling is enabled, and if new codec flag is not
826 // set.
827 const bool should_update_stats =
828 (enable_rtx_handling_ ||
829 static_cast<int32_t>(main_timestamp - timestamp_) >= 0) &&
830 !new_codec_;
831
832 auto relative_delay =
833 controller_->PacketArrived(fs_hz_, should_update_stats, info);
834 if (relative_delay) {
835 stats_->RelativePacketArrivalDelay(relative_delay.value());
836 }
837 return 0;
838}
839
840int NetEqImpl::GetAudioInternal(AudioFrame* audio_frame,
841 bool* muted,
842 absl::optional<Operation> action_override) {
843 PacketList packet_list;
844 DtmfEvent dtmf_event;
845 Operation operation;
846 bool play_dtmf;
847 *muted = false;
848 last_decoded_timestamps_.clear();
849 last_decoded_packet_infos_.clear();
850 tick_timer_->Increment();
851 stats_->IncreaseCounter(output_size_samples_, fs_hz_);
852 const auto lifetime_stats = stats_->GetLifetimeStatistics();
853 expand_uma_logger_.UpdateSampleCounter(lifetime_stats.concealed_samples,
854 fs_hz_);
855 speech_expand_uma_logger_.UpdateSampleCounter(
856 lifetime_stats.concealed_samples -
857 lifetime_stats.silent_concealed_samples,
858 fs_hz_);
859
860 // Check for muted state.
861 if (enable_muted_state_ && expand_->Muted() && packet_buffer_->Empty()) {
862 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(last_mode_, Mode::kExpand);
863 audio_frame->Reset();
864 RTC_DCHECK(audio_frame->muted()); // Reset() should mute the frame.
865 playout_timestamp_ += static_cast<uint32_t>(output_size_samples_);
866 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_ = fs_hz_;
867 audio_frame->samples_per_channel_ = output_size_samples_;
868 audio_frame->timestamp_ =
869 first_packet_
870 ? 0
871 : timestamp_scaler_->ToExternal(playout_timestamp_) -
872 static_cast<uint32_t>(audio_frame->samples_per_channel_);
873 audio_frame->num_channels_ = sync_buffer_->Channels();
874 stats_->ExpandedNoiseSamples(output_size_samples_, false);
875 controller_->NotifyMutedState();
876 *muted = true;
877 return 0;
878 }
879 int return_value = GetDecision(&operation, &packet_list, &dtmf_event,
880 &play_dtmf, action_override);
881 if (return_value != 0) {
882 last_mode_ = Mode::kError;
883 return return_value;
884 }
885
886 AudioDecoder::SpeechType speech_type;
887 int length = 0;
888 const size_t start_num_packets = packet_list.size();
889 int decode_return_value =
890 Decode(&packet_list, &operation, &length, &speech_type);
891
892 assert(vad_.get());
893 bool sid_frame_available =
894 (operation == Operation::kRfc3389Cng && !packet_list.empty());
895 vad_->Update(decoded_buffer_.get(), static_cast<size_t>(length), speech_type,
896 sid_frame_available, fs_hz_);
897
898 // This is the criterion that we did decode some data through the speech
899 // decoder, and the operation resulted in comfort noise.
900 const bool codec_internal_sid_frame =
901 (speech_type == AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise &&
902 start_num_packets > packet_list.size());
903
904 if (sid_frame_available || codec_internal_sid_frame) {
905 // Start a new stopwatch since we are decoding a new CNG packet.
906 generated_noise_stopwatch_ = tick_timer_->GetNewStopwatch();
907 }
908
909 algorithm_buffer_->Clear();
910 switch (operation) {
911 case Operation::kNormal: {
912 DoNormal(decoded_buffer_.get(), length, speech_type, play_dtmf);
913 if (length > 0) {
914 stats_->DecodedOutputPlayed();
915 }
916 break;
917 }
918 case Operation::kMerge: {
919 DoMerge(decoded_buffer_.get(), length, speech_type, play_dtmf);
920 break;
921 }
922 case Operation::kExpand: {
923 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(return_value, 0);
924 if (!current_rtp_payload_type_ || !DoCodecPlc()) {
925 return_value = DoExpand(play_dtmf);
926 }
927 RTC_DCHECK_GE(sync_buffer_->FutureLength() - expand_->overlap_length(),
928 output_size_samples_);
929 break;
930 }
931 case Operation::kAccelerate:
932 case Operation::kFastAccelerate: {
933 const bool fast_accelerate =
934 enable_fast_accelerate_ && (operation == Operation::kFastAccelerate);
935 return_value = DoAccelerate(decoded_buffer_.get(), length, speech_type,
936 play_dtmf, fast_accelerate);
937 break;
938 }
939 case Operation::kPreemptiveExpand: {
940 return_value = DoPreemptiveExpand(decoded_buffer_.get(), length,
941 speech_type, play_dtmf);
942 break;
943 }
944 case Operation::kRfc3389Cng:
945 case Operation::kRfc3389CngNoPacket: {
946 return_value = DoRfc3389Cng(&packet_list, play_dtmf);
947 break;
948 }
949 case Operation::kCodecInternalCng: {
950 // This handles the case when there is no transmission and the decoder
951 // should produce internal comfort noise.
952 // TODO(hlundin): Write test for codec-internal CNG.
953 DoCodecInternalCng(decoded_buffer_.get(), length);
954 break;
955 }
956 case Operation::kDtmf: {
957 // TODO(hlundin): Write test for this.
958 return_value = DoDtmf(dtmf_event, &play_dtmf);
959 break;
960 }
961 case Operation::kUndefined: {
962 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Invalid operation kUndefined.";
963 assert(false); // This should not happen.
964 last_mode_ = Mode::kError;
965 return kInvalidOperation;
966 }
967 } // End of switch.
968 last_operation_ = operation;
969 if (return_value < 0) {
970 return return_value;
971 }
972
973 if (last_mode_ != Mode::kRfc3389Cng) {
974 comfort_noise_->Reset();
975 }
976
977 // We treat it as if all packets referenced to by |last_decoded_packet_infos_|
978 // were mashed together when creating the samples in |algorithm_buffer_|.
979 RtpPacketInfos packet_infos(last_decoded_packet_infos_);
980
981 // Copy samples from |algorithm_buffer_| to |sync_buffer_|.
982 //
983 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10757):
984 // We would in the future also like to pass |packet_infos| so that we can do
985 // sample-perfect tracking of that information across |sync_buffer_|.
986 sync_buffer_->PushBack(*algorithm_buffer_);
987
988 // Extract data from |sync_buffer_| to |output|.
989 size_t num_output_samples_per_channel = output_size_samples_;
990 size_t num_output_samples = output_size_samples_ * sync_buffer_->Channels();
991 if (num_output_samples > AudioFrame::kMaxDataSizeSamples) {
992 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Output array is too short. "
993 << AudioFrame::kMaxDataSizeSamples << " < "
994 << output_size_samples_ << " * "
995 << sync_buffer_->Channels();
996 num_output_samples = AudioFrame::kMaxDataSizeSamples;
997 num_output_samples_per_channel =
998 AudioFrame::kMaxDataSizeSamples / sync_buffer_->Channels();
999 }
1000 sync_buffer_->GetNextAudioInterleaved(num_output_samples_per_channel,
1001 audio_frame);
1002 audio_frame->sample_rate_hz_ = fs_hz_;
1003 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10757):
1004 // We don't have the ability to properly track individual packets once their
1005 // audio samples have entered |sync_buffer_|. So for now, treat it as if
1006 // |packet_infos| from packets decoded by the current |GetAudioInternal()|
1007 // call were all consumed assembling the current audio frame and the current
1008 // audio frame only.
1009 audio_frame->packet_infos_ = std::move(packet_infos);
1010 if (sync_buffer_->FutureLength() < expand_->overlap_length()) {
1011 // The sync buffer should always contain |overlap_length| samples, but now
1012 // too many samples have been extracted. Reinstall the |overlap_length|
1013 // lookahead by moving the index.
1014 const size_t missing_lookahead_samples =
1015 expand_->overlap_length() - sync_buffer_->FutureLength();
1016 RTC_DCHECK_GE(sync_buffer_->next_index(), missing_lookahead_samples);
1017 sync_buffer_->set_next_index(sync_buffer_->next_index() -
1018 missing_lookahead_samples);
1019 }
1020 if (audio_frame->samples_per_channel_ != output_size_samples_) {
1021 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "audio_frame->samples_per_channel_ ("
1022 << audio_frame->samples_per_channel_
1023 << ") != output_size_samples_ (" << output_size_samples_
1024 << ")";
1025 // TODO(minyue): treatment of under-run, filling zeros
1026 audio_frame->Mute();
1027 return kSampleUnderrun;
1028 }
1029
1030 // Should always have overlap samples left in the |sync_buffer_|.
1031 RTC_DCHECK_GE(sync_buffer_->FutureLength(), expand_->overlap_length());
1032
1033 // TODO(yujo): For muted frames, this can be a copy rather than an addition.
1034 if (play_dtmf) {
1035 return_value = DtmfOverdub(dtmf_event, sync_buffer_->Channels(),
1036 audio_frame->mutable_data());
1037 }
1038
1039 // Update the background noise parameters if last operation wrote data
1040 // straight from the decoder to the |sync_buffer_|. That is, none of the
1041 // operations that modify the signal can be followed by a parameter update.
1042 if ((last_mode_ == Mode::kNormal) || (last_mode_ == Mode::kAccelerateFail) ||
1043 (last_mode_ == Mode::kPreemptiveExpandFail) ||
1044 (last_mode_ == Mode::kRfc3389Cng) ||
1045 (last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecInternalCng)) {
1046 background_noise_->Update(*sync_buffer_, *vad_.get());
1047 }
1048
1049 if (operation == Operation::kDtmf) {
1050 // DTMF data was written the end of |sync_buffer_|.
1051 // Update index to end of DTMF data in |sync_buffer_|.
1052 sync_buffer_->set_dtmf_index(sync_buffer_->Size());
1053 }
1054
1055 if (last_mode_ != Mode::kExpand && last_mode_ != Mode::kCodecPlc) {
1056 // If last operation was not expand, calculate the |playout_timestamp_| from
1057 // the |sync_buffer_|. However, do not update the |playout_timestamp_| if it
1058 // would be moved "backwards".
1059 uint32_t temp_timestamp =
1060 sync_buffer_->end_timestamp() -
1061 static_cast<uint32_t>(sync_buffer_->FutureLength());
1062 if (static_cast<int32_t>(temp_timestamp - playout_timestamp_) > 0) {
1063 playout_timestamp_ = temp_timestamp;
1064 }
1065 } else {
1066 // Use dead reckoning to estimate the |playout_timestamp_|.
1067 playout_timestamp_ += static_cast<uint32_t>(output_size_samples_);
1068 }
1069 // Set the timestamp in the audio frame to zero before the first packet has
1070 // been inserted. Otherwise, subtract the frame size in samples to get the
1071 // timestamp of the first sample in the frame (playout_timestamp_ is the
1072 // last + 1).
1073 audio_frame->timestamp_ =
1074 first_packet_
1075 ? 0
1076 : timestamp_scaler_->ToExternal(playout_timestamp_) -
1077 static_cast<uint32_t>(audio_frame->samples_per_channel_);
1078
1079 if (!(last_mode_ == Mode::kRfc3389Cng ||
1080 last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecInternalCng || last_mode_ == Mode::kExpand ||
1081 last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecPlc)) {
1082 generated_noise_stopwatch_.reset();
1083 }
1084
1085 if (decode_return_value)
1086 return decode_return_value;
1087 return return_value;
1088}
1089
1090int NetEqImpl::GetDecision(Operation* operation,
1091 PacketList* packet_list,
1092 DtmfEvent* dtmf_event,
1093 bool* play_dtmf,
1094 absl::optional<Operation> action_override) {
1095 // Initialize output variables.
1096 *play_dtmf = false;
1097 *operation = Operation::kUndefined;
1098
1099 assert(sync_buffer_.get());
1100 uint32_t end_timestamp = sync_buffer_->end_timestamp();
1101 if (!new_codec_) {
1102 const uint32_t five_seconds_samples = 5 * fs_hz_;
1103 packet_buffer_->DiscardOldPackets(end_timestamp, five_seconds_samples,
1104 stats_.get());
1105 }
1106 const Packet* packet = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket();
1107
1108 RTC_DCHECK(!generated_noise_stopwatch_ ||
1109 generated_noise_stopwatch_->ElapsedTicks() >= 1);
1110 uint64_t generated_noise_samples =
1111 generated_noise_stopwatch_ ? (generated_noise_stopwatch_->ElapsedTicks() -
1112 1) * output_size_samples_ +
1113 controller_->noise_fast_forward()
1114 : 0;
1115
1116 if (controller_->CngRfc3389On() || last_mode_ == Mode::kRfc3389Cng) {
1117 // Because of timestamp peculiarities, we have to "manually" disallow using
1118 // a CNG packet with the same timestamp as the one that was last played.
1119 // This can happen when using redundancy and will cause the timing to shift.
1120 while (packet && decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(packet->payload_type) &&
1121 (end_timestamp >= packet->timestamp ||
1122 end_timestamp + generated_noise_samples > packet->timestamp)) {
1123 // Don't use this packet, discard it.
1124 if (packet_buffer_->DiscardNextPacket(stats_.get()) !=
1125 PacketBuffer::kOK) {
1126 assert(false); // Must be ok by design.
1127 }
1128 // Check buffer again.
1129 if (!new_codec_) {
1130 packet_buffer_->DiscardOldPackets(end_timestamp, 5 * fs_hz_,
1131 stats_.get());
1132 }
1133 packet = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket();
1134 }
1135 }
1136
1137 assert(expand_.get());
1138 const int samples_left = static_cast<int>(sync_buffer_->FutureLength() -
1139 expand_->overlap_length());
1140 if (last_mode_ == Mode::kAccelerateSuccess ||
1141 last_mode_ == Mode::kAccelerateLowEnergy ||
1142 last_mode_ == Mode::kPreemptiveExpandSuccess ||
1143 last_mode_ == Mode::kPreemptiveExpandLowEnergy) {
1144 // Subtract (samples_left + output_size_samples_) from sampleMemory.
1145 controller_->AddSampleMemory(
1146 -(samples_left + rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(output_size_samples_)));
1147 }
1148
1149 // Check if it is time to play a DTMF event.
1150 if (dtmf_buffer_->GetEvent(
1151 static_cast<uint32_t>(end_timestamp + generated_noise_samples),
1152 dtmf_event)) {
1153 *play_dtmf = true;
1154 }
1155
1156 // Get instruction.
1157 assert(sync_buffer_.get());
1158 assert(expand_.get());
1159 generated_noise_samples =
1160 generated_noise_stopwatch_
1161 ? generated_noise_stopwatch_->ElapsedTicks() * output_size_samples_ +
1162 controller_->noise_fast_forward()
1163 : 0;
1164 NetEqController::NetEqStatus status;
1165 status.packet_buffer_info.dtx_or_cng =
1166 packet_buffer_->ContainsDtxOrCngPacket(decoder_database_.get());
1167 status.packet_buffer_info.num_samples =
1168 packet_buffer_->NumSamplesInBuffer(decoder_frame_length_);
1169 status.packet_buffer_info.span_samples = packet_buffer_->GetSpanSamples(
1170 decoder_frame_length_, last_output_sample_rate_hz_, true);
1171 status.packet_buffer_info.span_samples_no_dtx =
1172 packet_buffer_->GetSpanSamples(decoder_frame_length_,
1173 last_output_sample_rate_hz_, false);
1174 status.packet_buffer_info.num_packets = packet_buffer_->NumPacketsInBuffer();
1175 status.target_timestamp = sync_buffer_->end_timestamp();
1176 status.expand_mutefactor = expand_->MuteFactor(0);
1177 status.last_packet_samples = decoder_frame_length_;
1178 status.last_mode = last_mode_;
1179 status.play_dtmf = *play_dtmf;
1180 status.generated_noise_samples = generated_noise_samples;
1181 status.sync_buffer_samples = sync_buffer_->FutureLength();
1182 if (packet) {
1183 status.next_packet = {
1184 packet->timestamp, packet->frame && packet->frame->IsDtxPacket(),
1185 decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(packet->payload_type)};
1186 }
1187 *operation = controller_->GetDecision(status, &reset_decoder_);
1188
1189 // Disallow time stretching if this packet is DTX, because such a decision may
1190 // be based on earlier buffer level estimate, as we do not update buffer level
1191 // during DTX. When we have a better way to update buffer level during DTX,
1192 // this can be discarded.
1193 if (packet && packet->frame && packet->frame->IsDtxPacket() &&
1194 (*operation == Operation::kMerge ||
1195 *operation == Operation::kAccelerate ||
1196 *operation == Operation::kFastAccelerate ||
1197 *operation == Operation::kPreemptiveExpand)) {
1198 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1199 }
1200
1201 if (action_override) {
1202 // Use the provided action instead of the decision NetEq decided on.
1203 *operation = *action_override;
1204 }
1205 // Check if we already have enough samples in the |sync_buffer_|. If so,
1206 // change decision to normal, unless the decision was merge, accelerate, or
1207 // preemptive expand.
1208 if (samples_left >= rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(output_size_samples_) &&
1209 *operation != Operation::kMerge && *operation != Operation::kAccelerate &&
1210 *operation != Operation::kFastAccelerate &&
1211 *operation != Operation::kPreemptiveExpand) {
1212 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1213 return 0;
1214 }
1215
1216 controller_->ExpandDecision(*operation);
1217 if ((last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecPlc) && (*operation != Operation::kExpand)) {
1218 // Getting out of the PLC expand mode, reporting interruptions.
1219 // NetEq PLC reports this metrics in expand.cc
1220 stats_->EndExpandEvent(fs_hz_);
1221 }
1222
1223 // Check conditions for reset.
1224 if (new_codec_ || *operation == Operation::kUndefined) {
1225 // The only valid reason to get kUndefined is that new_codec_ is set.
1226 assert(new_codec_);
1227 if (*play_dtmf && !packet) {
1228 timestamp_ = dtmf_event->timestamp;
1229 } else {
1230 if (!packet) {
1231 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Packet missing where it shouldn't.";
1232 return -1;
1233 }
1234 timestamp_ = packet->timestamp;
1235 if (*operation == Operation::kRfc3389CngNoPacket &&
1236 decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(packet->payload_type)) {
1237 // Change decision to CNG packet, since we do have a CNG packet, but it
1238 // was considered too early to use. Now, use it anyway.
1239 *operation = Operation::kRfc3389Cng;
1240 } else if (*operation != Operation::kRfc3389Cng) {
1241 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1242 }
1243 }
1244 // Adjust |sync_buffer_| timestamp before setting |end_timestamp| to the
1245 // new value.
1246 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(timestamp_ - end_timestamp);
1247 end_timestamp = timestamp_;
1248 new_codec_ = false;
1249 controller_->SoftReset();
1250 stats_->ResetMcu();
1251 }
1252
1253 size_t required_samples = output_size_samples_;
1254 const size_t samples_10_ms = static_cast<size_t>(80 * fs_mult_);
1255 const size_t samples_20_ms = 2 * samples_10_ms;
1256 const size_t samples_30_ms = 3 * samples_10_ms;
1257
1258 switch (*operation) {
1259 case Operation::kExpand: {
1260 timestamp_ = end_timestamp;
1261 return 0;
1262 }
1263 case Operation::kRfc3389CngNoPacket:
1264 case Operation::kCodecInternalCng: {
1265 return 0;
1266 }
1267 case Operation::kDtmf: {
1268 // TODO(hlundin): Write test for this.
1269 // Update timestamp.
1270 timestamp_ = end_timestamp;
1271 const uint64_t generated_noise_samples =
1272 generated_noise_stopwatch_
1273 ? generated_noise_stopwatch_->ElapsedTicks() *
1274 output_size_samples_ +
1275 controller_->noise_fast_forward()
1276 : 0;
1277 if (generated_noise_samples > 0 && last_mode_ != Mode::kDtmf) {
1278 // Make a jump in timestamp due to the recently played comfort noise.
1279 uint32_t timestamp_jump =
1280 static_cast<uint32_t>(generated_noise_samples);
1281 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(timestamp_jump);
1282 timestamp_ += timestamp_jump;
1283 }
1284 return 0;
1285 }
1286 case Operation::kAccelerate:
1287 case Operation::kFastAccelerate: {
1288 // In order to do an accelerate we need at least 30 ms of audio data.
1289 if (samples_left >= static_cast<int>(samples_30_ms)) {
1290 // Already have enough data, so we do not need to extract any more.
1291 controller_->set_sample_memory(samples_left);
1292 controller_->set_prev_time_scale(true);
1293 return 0;
1294 } else if (samples_left >= static_cast<int>(samples_10_ms) &&
1295 decoder_frame_length_ >= samples_30_ms) {
1296 // Avoid decoding more data as it might overflow the playout buffer.
1297 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1298 return 0;
1299 } else if (samples_left < static_cast<int>(samples_20_ms) &&
1300 decoder_frame_length_ < samples_30_ms) {
1301 // Build up decoded data by decoding at least 20 ms of audio data. Do
1302 // not perform accelerate yet, but wait until we only need to do one
1303 // decoding.
1304 required_samples = 2 * output_size_samples_;
1305 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1306 }
1307 // If none of the above is true, we have one of two possible situations:
1308 // (1) 20 ms <= samples_left < 30 ms and decoder_frame_length_ < 30 ms; or
1309 // (2) samples_left < 10 ms and decoder_frame_length_ >= 30 ms.
1310 // In either case, we move on with the accelerate decision, and decode one
1311 // frame now.
1312 break;
1313 }
1314 case Operation::kPreemptiveExpand: {
1315 // In order to do a preemptive expand we need at least 30 ms of decoded
1316 // audio data.
1317 if ((samples_left >= static_cast<int>(samples_30_ms)) ||
1318 (samples_left >= static_cast<int>(samples_10_ms) &&
1319 decoder_frame_length_ >= samples_30_ms)) {
1320 // Already have enough data, so we do not need to extract any more.
1321 // Or, avoid decoding more data as it might overflow the playout buffer.
1322 // Still try preemptive expand, though.
1323 controller_->set_sample_memory(samples_left);
1324 controller_->set_prev_time_scale(true);
1325 return 0;
1326 }
1327 if (samples_left < static_cast<int>(samples_20_ms) &&
1328 decoder_frame_length_ < samples_30_ms) {
1329 // Build up decoded data by decoding at least 20 ms of audio data.
1330 // Still try to perform preemptive expand.
1331 required_samples = 2 * output_size_samples_;
1332 }
1333 // Move on with the preemptive expand decision.
1334 break;
1335 }
1336 case Operation::kMerge: {
1337 required_samples =
1338 std::max(merge_->RequiredFutureSamples(), required_samples);
1339 break;
1340 }
1341 default: {
1342 // Do nothing.
1343 }
1344 }
1345
1346 // Get packets from buffer.
1347 int extracted_samples = 0;
1348 if (packet) {
1349 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(packet->timestamp - end_timestamp);
1350
1351 if (*operation != Operation::kRfc3389Cng) {
1352 // We are about to decode and use a non-CNG packet.
1353 controller_->SetCngOff();
1354 }
1355
1356 extracted_samples = ExtractPackets(required_samples, packet_list);
1357 if (extracted_samples < 0) {
1358 return kPacketBufferCorruption;
1359 }
1360 }
1361
1362 if (*operation == Operation::kAccelerate ||
1363 *operation == Operation::kFastAccelerate ||
1364 *operation == Operation::kPreemptiveExpand) {
1365 controller_->set_sample_memory(samples_left + extracted_samples);
1366 controller_->set_prev_time_scale(true);
1367 }
1368
1369 if (*operation == Operation::kAccelerate ||
1370 *operation == Operation::kFastAccelerate) {
1371 // Check that we have enough data (30ms) to do accelerate.
1372 if (extracted_samples + samples_left < static_cast<int>(samples_30_ms)) {
1373 // TODO(hlundin): Write test for this.
1374 // Not enough, do normal operation instead.
1375 *operation = Operation::kNormal;
1376 }
1377 }
1378
1379 timestamp_ = end_timestamp;
1380 return 0;
1381}
1382
1383int NetEqImpl::Decode(PacketList* packet_list,
1384 Operation* operation,
1385 int* decoded_length,
1386 AudioDecoder::SpeechType* speech_type) {
1387 *speech_type = AudioDecoder::kSpeech;
1388
1389 // When packet_list is empty, we may be in kCodecInternalCng mode, and for
1390 // that we use current active decoder.
1391 AudioDecoder* decoder = decoder_database_->GetActiveDecoder();
1392
1393 if (!packet_list->empty()) {
1394 const Packet& packet = packet_list->front();
1395 uint8_t payload_type = packet.payload_type;
1396 if (!decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(payload_type)) {
1397 decoder = decoder_database_->GetDecoder(payload_type);
1398 assert(decoder);
1399 if (!decoder) {
1400 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1401 << "Unknown payload type " << static_cast<int>(payload_type);
1402 packet_list->clear();
1403 return kDecoderNotFound;
1404 }
1405 bool decoder_changed;
1406 decoder_database_->SetActiveDecoder(payload_type, &decoder_changed);
1407 if (decoder_changed) {
1408 // We have a new decoder. Re-init some values.
1409 const DecoderDatabase::DecoderInfo* decoder_info =
1410 decoder_database_->GetDecoderInfo(payload_type);
1411 assert(decoder_info);
1412 if (!decoder_info) {
1413 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1414 << "Unknown payload type " << static_cast<int>(payload_type);
1415 packet_list->clear();
1416 return kDecoderNotFound;
1417 }
1418 // If sampling rate or number of channels has changed, we need to make
1419 // a reset.
1420 if (decoder_info->SampleRateHz() != fs_hz_ ||
1421 decoder->Channels() != algorithm_buffer_->Channels()) {
1422 // TODO(tlegrand): Add unittest to cover this event.
1423 SetSampleRateAndChannels(decoder_info->SampleRateHz(),
1424 decoder->Channels());
1425 }
1426 sync_buffer_->set_end_timestamp(timestamp_);
1427 playout_timestamp_ = timestamp_;
1428 }
1429 }
1430 }
1431
1432 if (reset_decoder_) {
1433 // TODO(hlundin): Write test for this.
1434 if (decoder)
1435 decoder->Reset();
1436
1437 // Reset comfort noise decoder.
1438 ComfortNoiseDecoder* cng_decoder = decoder_database_->GetActiveCngDecoder();
1439 if (cng_decoder)
1440 cng_decoder->Reset();
1441
1442 reset_decoder_ = false;
1443 }
1444
1445 *decoded_length = 0;
1446 // Update codec-internal PLC state.
1447 if ((*operation == Operation::kMerge) && decoder && decoder->HasDecodePlc()) {
1448 decoder->DecodePlc(1, &decoded_buffer_[*decoded_length]);
1449 }
1450
1451 int return_value;
1452 if (*operation == Operation::kCodecInternalCng) {
1453 RTC_DCHECK(packet_list->empty());
1454 return_value = DecodeCng(decoder, decoded_length, speech_type);
1455 } else {
1456 return_value = DecodeLoop(packet_list, *operation, decoder, decoded_length,
1457 speech_type);
1458 }
1459
1460 if (*decoded_length < 0) {
1461 // Error returned from the decoder.
1462 *decoded_length = 0;
1463 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(
1464 static_cast<uint32_t>(decoder_frame_length_));
1465 int error_code = 0;
1466 if (decoder)
1467 error_code = decoder->ErrorCode();
1468 if (error_code != 0) {
1469 // Got some error code from the decoder.
1470 return_value = kDecoderErrorCode;
1471 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Decoder returned error code: " << error_code;
1472 } else {
1473 // Decoder does not implement error codes. Return generic error.
1474 return_value = kOtherDecoderError;
1475 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Decoder error (no error code)";
1476 }
1477 *operation = Operation::kExpand; // Do expansion to get data instead.
1478 }
1479 if (*speech_type != AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise) {
1480 // Don't increment timestamp if codec returned CNG speech type
1481 // since in this case, the we will increment the CNGplayedTS counter.
1482 // Increase with number of samples per channel.
1483 assert(*decoded_length == 0 ||
1484 (decoder && decoder->Channels() == sync_buffer_->Channels()));
1485 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(
1486 *decoded_length / static_cast<int>(sync_buffer_->Channels()));
1487 }
1488 return return_value;
1489}
1490
1491int NetEqImpl::DecodeCng(AudioDecoder* decoder,
1492 int* decoded_length,
1493 AudioDecoder::SpeechType* speech_type) {
1494 if (!decoder) {
1495 // This happens when active decoder is not defined.
1496 *decoded_length = -1;
1497 return 0;
1498 }
1499
1500 while (*decoded_length < rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(output_size_samples_)) {
1501 const int length = decoder->Decode(
1502 nullptr, 0, fs_hz_,
1503 (decoded_buffer_length_ - *decoded_length) * sizeof(int16_t),
1504 &decoded_buffer_[*decoded_length], speech_type);
1505 if (length > 0) {
1506 *decoded_length += length;
1507 } else {
1508 // Error.
1509 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to decode CNG";
1510 *decoded_length = -1;
1511 break;
1512 }
1513 if (*decoded_length > static_cast<int>(decoded_buffer_length_)) {
1514 // Guard against overflow.
1515 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Decoded too much CNG.";
1516 return kDecodedTooMuch;
1517 }
1518 }
1519 return 0;
1520}
1521
1522int NetEqImpl::DecodeLoop(PacketList* packet_list,
1523 const Operation& operation,
1524 AudioDecoder* decoder,
1525 int* decoded_length,
1526 AudioDecoder::SpeechType* speech_type) {
1527 RTC_DCHECK(last_decoded_timestamps_.empty());
1528 RTC_DCHECK(last_decoded_packet_infos_.empty());
1529
1530 // Do decoding.
1531 while (!packet_list->empty() && !decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(
1532 packet_list->front().payload_type)) {
1533 assert(decoder); // At this point, we must have a decoder object.
1534 // The number of channels in the |sync_buffer_| should be the same as the
1535 // number decoder channels.
1536 assert(sync_buffer_->Channels() == decoder->Channels());
1537 assert(decoded_buffer_length_ >= kMaxFrameSize * decoder->Channels());
1538 assert(operation == Operation::kNormal ||
1539 operation == Operation::kAccelerate ||
1540 operation == Operation::kFastAccelerate ||
1541 operation == Operation::kMerge ||
1542 operation == Operation::kPreemptiveExpand);
1543
1544 auto opt_result = packet_list->front().frame->Decode(
1545 rtc::ArrayView<int16_t>(&decoded_buffer_[*decoded_length],
1546 decoded_buffer_length_ - *decoded_length));
1547 last_decoded_timestamps_.push_back(packet_list->front().timestamp);
1548 last_decoded_packet_infos_.push_back(
1549 std::move(packet_list->front().packet_info));
1550 packet_list->pop_front();
1551 if (opt_result) {
1552 const auto& result = *opt_result;
1553 *speech_type = result.speech_type;
1554 if (result.num_decoded_samples > 0) {
1555 *decoded_length += rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(result.num_decoded_samples);
1556 // Update |decoder_frame_length_| with number of samples per channel.
1557 decoder_frame_length_ =
1558 result.num_decoded_samples / decoder->Channels();
1559 }
1560 } else {
1561 // Error.
1562 // TODO(ossu): What to put here?
1563 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Decode error";
1564 *decoded_length = -1;
1565 last_decoded_packet_infos_.clear();
1566 packet_list->clear();
1567 break;
1568 }
1569 if (*decoded_length > rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(decoded_buffer_length_)) {
1570 // Guard against overflow.
1571 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Decoded too much.";
1572 packet_list->clear();
1573 return kDecodedTooMuch;
1574 }
1575 } // End of decode loop.
1576
1577 // If the list is not empty at this point, either a decoding error terminated
1578 // the while-loop, or list must hold exactly one CNG packet.
1579 assert(packet_list->empty() || *decoded_length < 0 ||
1580 (packet_list->size() == 1 && decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(
1581 packet_list->front().payload_type)));
1582 return 0;
1583}
1584
1585void NetEqImpl::DoNormal(const int16_t* decoded_buffer,
1586 size_t decoded_length,
1587 AudioDecoder::SpeechType speech_type,
1588 bool play_dtmf) {
1589 assert(normal_.get());
1590 normal_->Process(decoded_buffer, decoded_length, last_mode_,
1591 algorithm_buffer_.get());
1592 if (decoded_length != 0) {
1593 last_mode_ = Mode::kNormal;
1594 }
1595
1596 // If last packet was decoded as an inband CNG, set mode to CNG instead.
1597 if ((speech_type == AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise) ||
1598 ((last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecInternalCng) && (decoded_length == 0))) {
1599 // TODO(hlundin): Remove second part of || statement above.
1600 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecInternalCng;
1601 }
1602
1603 if (!play_dtmf) {
1604 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1605 }
1606}
1607
1608void NetEqImpl::DoMerge(int16_t* decoded_buffer,
1609 size_t decoded_length,
1610 AudioDecoder::SpeechType speech_type,
1611 bool play_dtmf) {
1612 assert(merge_.get());
1613 size_t new_length =
1614 merge_->Process(decoded_buffer, decoded_length, algorithm_buffer_.get());
1615 // Correction can be negative.
1616 int expand_length_correction =
1617 rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(new_length) -
1618 rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(decoded_length / algorithm_buffer_->Channels());
1619
1620 // Update in-call and post-call statistics.
1621 if (expand_->MuteFactor(0) == 0) {
1622 // Expand generates only noise.
1623 stats_->ExpandedNoiseSamplesCorrection(expand_length_correction);
1624 } else {
1625 // Expansion generates more than only noise.
1626 stats_->ExpandedVoiceSamplesCorrection(expand_length_correction);
1627 }
1628
1629 last_mode_ = Mode::kMerge;
1630 // If last packet was decoded as an inband CNG, set mode to CNG instead.
1631 if (speech_type == AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise) {
1632 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecInternalCng;
1633 }
1634 expand_->Reset();
1635 if (!play_dtmf) {
1636 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1637 }
1638}
1639
1640bool NetEqImpl::DoCodecPlc() {
1641 AudioDecoder* decoder = decoder_database_->GetActiveDecoder();
1642 if (!decoder) {
1643 return false;
1644 }
1645 const size_t channels = algorithm_buffer_->Channels();
1646 const size_t requested_samples_per_channel =
1647 output_size_samples_ -
1648 (sync_buffer_->FutureLength() - expand_->overlap_length());
1649 concealment_audio_.Clear();
1650 decoder->GeneratePlc(requested_samples_per_channel, &concealment_audio_);
1651 if (concealment_audio_.empty()) {
1652 // Nothing produced. Resort to regular expand.
1653 return false;
1654 }
1655 RTC_CHECK_GE(concealment_audio_.size(),
1656 requested_samples_per_channel * channels);
1657 sync_buffer_->PushBackInterleaved(concealment_audio_);
1658 RTC_DCHECK_NE(algorithm_buffer_->Channels(), 0);
1659 const size_t concealed_samples_per_channel =
1660 concealment_audio_.size() / channels;
1661
1662 // Update in-call and post-call statistics.
1663 const bool is_new_concealment_event = (last_mode_ != Mode::kCodecPlc);
1664 if (std::all_of(concealment_audio_.cbegin(), concealment_audio_.cend(),
1665 [](int16_t i) { return i == 0; })) {
1666 // Expand operation generates only noise.
1667 stats_->ExpandedNoiseSamples(concealed_samples_per_channel,
1668 is_new_concealment_event);
1669 } else {
1670 // Expand operation generates more than only noise.
1671 stats_->ExpandedVoiceSamples(concealed_samples_per_channel,
1672 is_new_concealment_event);
1673 }
1674 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecPlc;
1675 if (!generated_noise_stopwatch_) {
1676 // Start a new stopwatch since we may be covering for a lost CNG packet.
1677 generated_noise_stopwatch_ = tick_timer_->GetNewStopwatch();
1678 }
1679 return true;
1680}
1681
1682int NetEqImpl::DoExpand(bool play_dtmf) {
1683 while ((sync_buffer_->FutureLength() - expand_->overlap_length()) <
1684 output_size_samples_) {
1685 algorithm_buffer_->Clear();
1686 int return_value = expand_->Process(algorithm_buffer_.get());
1687 size_t length = algorithm_buffer_->Size();
1688 bool is_new_concealment_event = (last_mode_ != Mode::kExpand);
1689
1690 // Update in-call and post-call statistics.
1691 if (expand_->MuteFactor(0) == 0) {
1692 // Expand operation generates only noise.
1693 stats_->ExpandedNoiseSamples(length, is_new_concealment_event);
1694 } else {
1695 // Expand operation generates more than only noise.
1696 stats_->ExpandedVoiceSamples(length, is_new_concealment_event);
1697 }
1698
1699 last_mode_ = Mode::kExpand;
1700
1701 if (return_value < 0) {
1702 return return_value;
1703 }
1704
1705 sync_buffer_->PushBack(*algorithm_buffer_);
1706 algorithm_buffer_->Clear();
1707 }
1708 if (!play_dtmf) {
1709 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1710 }
1711
1712 if (!generated_noise_stopwatch_) {
1713 // Start a new stopwatch since we may be covering for a lost CNG packet.
1714 generated_noise_stopwatch_ = tick_timer_->GetNewStopwatch();
1715 }
1716
1717 return 0;
1718}
1719
1720int NetEqImpl::DoAccelerate(int16_t* decoded_buffer,
1721 size_t decoded_length,
1722 AudioDecoder::SpeechType speech_type,
1723 bool play_dtmf,
1724 bool fast_accelerate) {
1725 const size_t required_samples =
1726 static_cast<size_t>(240 * fs_mult_); // Must have 30 ms.
1727 size_t borrowed_samples_per_channel = 0;
1728 size_t num_channels = algorithm_buffer_->Channels();
1729 size_t decoded_length_per_channel = decoded_length / num_channels;
1730 if (decoded_length_per_channel < required_samples) {
1731 // Must move data from the |sync_buffer_| in order to get 30 ms.
1732 borrowed_samples_per_channel =
1733 static_cast<int>(required_samples - decoded_length_per_channel);
1734 memmove(&decoded_buffer[borrowed_samples_per_channel * num_channels],
1735 decoded_buffer, sizeof(int16_t) * decoded_length);
1736 sync_buffer_->ReadInterleavedFromEnd(borrowed_samples_per_channel,
1737 decoded_buffer);
1738 decoded_length = required_samples * num_channels;
1739 }
1740
1741 size_t samples_removed = 0;
1742 Accelerate::ReturnCodes return_code =
1743 accelerate_->Process(decoded_buffer, decoded_length, fast_accelerate,
1744 algorithm_buffer_.get(), &samples_removed);
1745 stats_->AcceleratedSamples(samples_removed);
1746 switch (return_code) {
1747 case Accelerate::kSuccess:
1748 last_mode_ = Mode::kAccelerateSuccess;
1749 break;
1750 case Accelerate::kSuccessLowEnergy:
1751 last_mode_ = Mode::kAccelerateLowEnergy;
1752 break;
1753 case Accelerate::kNoStretch:
1754 last_mode_ = Mode::kAccelerateFail;
1755 break;
1756 case Accelerate::kError:
1757 // TODO(hlundin): Map to Modes::kError instead?
1758 last_mode_ = Mode::kAccelerateFail;
1759 return kAccelerateError;
1760 }
1761
1762 if (borrowed_samples_per_channel > 0) {
1763 // Copy borrowed samples back to the |sync_buffer_|.
1764 size_t length = algorithm_buffer_->Size();
1765 if (length < borrowed_samples_per_channel) {
1766 // This destroys the beginning of the buffer, but will not cause any
1767 // problems.
1768 sync_buffer_->ReplaceAtIndex(
1769 *algorithm_buffer_,
1770 sync_buffer_->Size() - borrowed_samples_per_channel);
1771 sync_buffer_->PushFrontZeros(borrowed_samples_per_channel - length);
1772 algorithm_buffer_->PopFront(length);
1773 assert(algorithm_buffer_->Empty());
1774 } else {
1775 sync_buffer_->ReplaceAtIndex(
1776 *algorithm_buffer_, borrowed_samples_per_channel,
1777 sync_buffer_->Size() - borrowed_samples_per_channel);
1778 algorithm_buffer_->PopFront(borrowed_samples_per_channel);
1779 }
1780 }
1781
1782 // If last packet was decoded as an inband CNG, set mode to CNG instead.
1783 if (speech_type == AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise) {
1784 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecInternalCng;
1785 }
1786 if (!play_dtmf) {
1787 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1788 }
1789 expand_->Reset();
1790 return 0;
1791}
1792
1793int NetEqImpl::DoPreemptiveExpand(int16_t* decoded_buffer,
1794 size_t decoded_length,
1795 AudioDecoder::SpeechType speech_type,
1796 bool play_dtmf) {
1797 const size_t required_samples =
1798 static_cast<size_t>(240 * fs_mult_); // Must have 30 ms.
1799 size_t num_channels = algorithm_buffer_->Channels();
1800 size_t borrowed_samples_per_channel = 0;
1801 size_t old_borrowed_samples_per_channel = 0;
1802 size_t decoded_length_per_channel = decoded_length / num_channels;
1803 if (decoded_length_per_channel < required_samples) {
1804 // Must move data from the |sync_buffer_| in order to get 30 ms.
1805 borrowed_samples_per_channel =
1806 required_samples - decoded_length_per_channel;
1807 // Calculate how many of these were already played out.
1808 old_borrowed_samples_per_channel =
1809 (borrowed_samples_per_channel > sync_buffer_->FutureLength())
1810 ? (borrowed_samples_per_channel - sync_buffer_->FutureLength())
1811 : 0;
1812 memmove(&decoded_buffer[borrowed_samples_per_channel * num_channels],
1813 decoded_buffer, sizeof(int16_t) * decoded_length);
1814 sync_buffer_->ReadInterleavedFromEnd(borrowed_samples_per_channel,
1815 decoded_buffer);
1816 decoded_length = required_samples * num_channels;
1817 }
1818
1819 size_t samples_added = 0;
1820 PreemptiveExpand::ReturnCodes return_code = preemptive_expand_->Process(
1821 decoded_buffer, decoded_length, old_borrowed_samples_per_channel,
1822 algorithm_buffer_.get(), &samples_added);
1823 stats_->PreemptiveExpandedSamples(samples_added);
1824 switch (return_code) {
1825 case PreemptiveExpand::kSuccess:
1826 last_mode_ = Mode::kPreemptiveExpandSuccess;
1827 break;
1828 case PreemptiveExpand::kSuccessLowEnergy:
1829 last_mode_ = Mode::kPreemptiveExpandLowEnergy;
1830 break;
1831 case PreemptiveExpand::kNoStretch:
1832 last_mode_ = Mode::kPreemptiveExpandFail;
1833 break;
1834 case PreemptiveExpand::kError:
1835 // TODO(hlundin): Map to Modes::kError instead?
1836 last_mode_ = Mode::kPreemptiveExpandFail;
1837 return kPreemptiveExpandError;
1838 }
1839
1840 if (borrowed_samples_per_channel > 0) {
1841 // Copy borrowed samples back to the |sync_buffer_|.
1842 sync_buffer_->ReplaceAtIndex(
1843 *algorithm_buffer_, borrowed_samples_per_channel,
1844 sync_buffer_->Size() - borrowed_samples_per_channel);
1845 algorithm_buffer_->PopFront(borrowed_samples_per_channel);
1846 }
1847
1848 // If last packet was decoded as an inband CNG, set mode to CNG instead.
1849 if (speech_type == AudioDecoder::kComfortNoise) {
1850 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecInternalCng;
1851 }
1852 if (!play_dtmf) {
1853 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1854 }
1855 expand_->Reset();
1856 return 0;
1857}
1858
1859int NetEqImpl::DoRfc3389Cng(PacketList* packet_list, bool play_dtmf) {
1860 if (!packet_list->empty()) {
1861 // Must have exactly one SID frame at this point.
1862 assert(packet_list->size() == 1);
1863 const Packet& packet = packet_list->front();
1864 if (!decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(packet.payload_type)) {
1865 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Trying to decode non-CNG payload as CNG.";
1866 return kOtherError;
1867 }
1868 if (comfort_noise_->UpdateParameters(packet) ==
1869 ComfortNoise::kInternalError) {
1870 algorithm_buffer_->Zeros(output_size_samples_);
1871 return -comfort_noise_->internal_error_code();
1872 }
1873 }
1874 int cn_return =
1875 comfort_noise_->Generate(output_size_samples_, algorithm_buffer_.get());
1876 expand_->Reset();
1877 last_mode_ = Mode::kRfc3389Cng;
1878 if (!play_dtmf) {
1879 dtmf_tone_generator_->Reset();
1880 }
1881 if (cn_return == ComfortNoise::kInternalError) {
1882 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Comfort noise generator returned error code: "
1883 << comfort_noise_->internal_error_code();
1884 return kComfortNoiseErrorCode;
1885 } else if (cn_return == ComfortNoise::kUnknownPayloadType) {
1886 return kUnknownRtpPayloadType;
1887 }
1888 return 0;
1889}

1891void NetEqImpl::DoCodecInternalCng(const int16_t* decoded_buffer,
1892 size_t decoded_length) {
1893 RTC_DCHECK(normal_.get());
1894 normal_->Process(decoded_buffer, decoded_length, last_mode_,
1895 algorithm_buffer_.get());
1896 last_mode_ = Mode::kCodecInternalCng;
1897 expand_->Reset();
1898}

1900int NetEqImpl::DoDtmf(const DtmfEvent& dtmf_event, bool* play_dtmf) {
1901 // This block of the code and the block further down, handling |dtmf_switch|
1902 // are commented out. Otherwise playing out-of-band DTMF would fail in VoE
1903 // test, DtmfTest.ManualSuccessfullySendsOutOfBandTelephoneEvents. This is
1904 // equivalent to |dtmf_switch| always be false.
1905 //
1906 // See http://webrtc-codereview.appspot.com/1195004/ for discussion
1907 // On this issue. This change might cause some glitches at the point of
1908 // switch from audio to DTMF. Issue 1545 is filed to track this.
1909 //
1910 // bool dtmf_switch = false;
1911 // if ((last_mode_ != Modes::kDtmf) &&
1912 // dtmf_tone_generator_->initialized()) {
1913 // // Special case; see below.
1914 // // We must catch this before calling Generate, since |initialized| is
1915 // // modified in that call.
1916 // dtmf_switch = true;
1917 // }
1918
1919 int dtmf_return_value = 0;
1920 if (!dtmf_tone_generator_->initialized()) {
1921 // Initialize if not already done.
1922 dtmf_return_value = dtmf_tone_generator_->Init(fs_hz_, dtmf_event.event_no,
1923 dtmf_event.volume);
1924 }
1925
1926 if (dtmf_return_value == 0) {
1927 // Generate DTMF signal.
1928 dtmf_return_value = dtmf_tone_generator_->Generate(output_size_samples_,
1929 algorithm_buffer_.get());
1930 }
1931
1932 if (dtmf_return_value < 0) {
1933 algorithm_buffer_->Zeros(output_size_samples_);
1934 return dtmf_return_value;
1935 }
1936
1937 // if (dtmf_switch) {
1938 // // This is the special case where the previous operation was DTMF
1939 // // overdub, but the current instruction is "regular" DTMF. We must make
1940 // // sure that the DTMF does not have any discontinuities. The first DTMF
1941 // // sample that we generate now must be played out immediately, therefore
1942 // // it must be copied to the speech buffer.
1943 // // TODO(hlundin): This code seems incorrect. (Legacy.) Write test and
1944 // // verify correct operation.
1945 // assert(false);
1946 // // Must generate enough data to replace all of the |sync_buffer_|
1947 // // "future".
1948 // int required_length = sync_buffer_->FutureLength();
1949 // assert(dtmf_tone_generator_->initialized());
1950 // dtmf_return_value = dtmf_tone_generator_->Generate(required_length,
1951 // algorithm_buffer_);
1952 // assert((size_t) required_length == algorithm_buffer_->Size());
1953 // if (dtmf_return_value < 0) {
1954 // algorithm_buffer_->Zeros(output_size_samples_);
1955 // return dtmf_return_value;
1956 // }
1957 //
1958 // // Overwrite the "future" part of the speech buffer with the new DTMF
1959 // // data.
1960 // // TODO(hlundin): It seems that this overwriting has gone lost.
1961 // // Not adapted for multi-channel yet.
1962 // assert(algorithm_buffer_->Channels() == 1);
1963 // if (algorithm_buffer_->Channels() != 1) {
1964 // RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "DTMF not supported for more than one channel";
1965 // return kStereoNotSupported;
1966 // }
1967 // // Shuffle the remaining data to the beginning of algorithm buffer.
1968 // algorithm_buffer_->PopFront(sync_buffer_->FutureLength());
1969 // }
1970
1971 sync_buffer_->IncreaseEndTimestamp(
1972 static_cast<uint32_t>(output_size_samples_));
1973 expand_->Reset();
1974 last_mode_ = Mode::kDtmf;
1975
1976 // Set to false because the DTMF is already in the algorithm buffer.
1977 *play_dtmf = false;
1978 return 0;
1979}

1981int NetEqImpl::DtmfOverdub(const DtmfEvent& dtmf_event,
1982 size_t num_channels,
1983 int16_t* output) const {
1984 size_t out_index = 0;
1985 size_t overdub_length = output_size_samples_; // Default value.
1986
1987 if (sync_buffer_->dtmf_index() > sync_buffer_->next_index()) {
1988 // Special operation for transition from "DTMF only" to "DTMF overdub".
1989 out_index =
1990 std::min(sync_buffer_->dtmf_index() - sync_buffer_->next_index(),
1991 output_size_samples_);
1992 overdub_length = output_size_samples_ - out_index;
1993 }
1994
1995 AudioMultiVector dtmf_output(num_channels);
1996 int dtmf_return_value = 0;
1997 if (!dtmf_tone_generator_->initialized()) {
1998 dtmf_return_value = dtmf_tone_generator_->Init(fs_hz_, dtmf_event.event_no,
1999 dtmf_event.volume);
2000 }
2001 if (dtmf_return_value == 0) {
2002 dtmf_return_value =
2003 dtmf_tone_generator_->Generate(overdub_length, &dtmf_output);
2004 assert(overdub_length == dtmf_output.Size());
2005 }
2006 dtmf_output.ReadInterleaved(overdub_length, &output[out_index]);
2007 return dtmf_return_value < 0 ? dtmf_return_value : 0;
2008}
2009
2010int NetEqImpl::ExtractPackets(size_t required_samples,
2011 PacketList* packet_list) {
2012 bool first_packet = true;
2013 uint8_t prev_payload_type = 0;
2014 uint32_t prev_timestamp = 0;
2015 uint16_t prev_sequence_number = 0;
2016 bool next_packet_available = false;
2017
2018 const Packet* next_packet = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket();
2019 RTC_DCHECK(next_packet);
2020 if (!next_packet) {
2021 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Packet buffer unexpectedly empty.";
2022 return -1;
2023 }
2024 uint32_t first_timestamp = next_packet->timestamp;
2025 size_t extracted_samples = 0;
2026
2027 // Packet extraction loop.
2028 do {
2029 timestamp_ = next_packet->timestamp;
2030 absl::optional<Packet> packet = packet_buffer_->GetNextPacket();
2031 // |next_packet| may be invalid after the |packet_buffer_| operation.
2032 next_packet = nullptr;
2033 if (!packet) {
2034 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Should always be able to extract a packet here";
2035 assert(false); // Should always be able to extract a packet here.
2036 return -1;
2037 }
2038 const uint64_t waiting_time_ms = packet->waiting_time->ElapsedMs();
2039 stats_->StoreWaitingTime(waiting_time_ms);
2040 RTC_DCHECK(!packet->empty());
2041
2042 if (first_packet) {
2043 first_packet = false;
2044 if (nack_enabled_) {
2045 RTC_DCHECK(nack_);
2046 // TODO(henrik.lundin): Should we update this for all decoded packets?
2047 nack_->UpdateLastDecodedPacket(packet->sequence_number,
2048 packet->timestamp);
2049 }
2050 prev_sequence_number = packet->sequence_number;
2051 prev_timestamp = packet->timestamp;
2052 prev_payload_type = packet->payload_type;
2053 }
2054
2055 const bool has_cng_packet =
2056 decoder_database_->IsComfortNoise(packet->payload_type);
2057 // Store number of extracted samples.
2058 size_t packet_duration = 0;
2059 if (packet->frame) {
2060 packet_duration = packet->frame->Duration();
2061 // TODO(ossu): Is this the correct way to track Opus FEC packets?
2062 if (packet->priority.codec_level > 0) {
2063 stats_->SecondaryDecodedSamples(
2064 rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(packet_duration));
2065 }
2066 } else if (!has_cng_packet) {
2067 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Unknown payload type "
2068 << static_cast<int>(packet->payload_type);
2069 RTC_NOTREACHED();
2070 }
2071
2072 if (packet_duration == 0) {
2073 // Decoder did not return a packet duration. Assume that the packet
2074 // contains the same number of samples as the previous one.
2075 packet_duration = decoder_frame_length_;
2076 }
2077 extracted_samples = packet->timestamp - first_timestamp + packet_duration;
2078
2079 RTC_DCHECK(controller_);
2080 stats_->JitterBufferDelay(
2081 packet_duration, waiting_time_ms + output_delay_chain_ms_,
2082 controller_->TargetLevelMs() + output_delay_chain_ms_);
2083
2084 packet_list->push_back(std::move(*packet)); // Store packet in list.
2085 packet = absl::nullopt; // Ensure it's never used after the move.
2086
2087 // Check what packet is available next.
2088 next_packet = packet_buffer_->PeekNextPacket();
2089 next_packet_available = false;
2090 if (next_packet && prev_payload_type == next_packet->payload_type &&
2091 !has_cng_packet) {
2092 int16_t seq_no_diff = next_packet->sequence_number - prev_sequence_number;
2093 size_t ts_diff = next_packet->timestamp - prev_timestamp;
2094 if ((seq_no_diff == 1 || seq_no_diff == 0) &&
2095 ts_diff <= packet_duration) {
2096 // The next sequence number is available, or the next part of a packet
2097 // that was split into pieces upon insertion.
2098 next_packet_available = true;
2099 }
2100 prev_sequence_number = next_packet->sequence_number;
2101 prev_timestamp = next_packet->timestamp;
2102 }
2103 } while (extracted_samples < required_samples && next_packet_available);
2104
2105 if (extracted_samples > 0) {
2106 // Delete old packets only when we are going to decode something. Otherwise,
2107 // we could end up in the situation where we never decode anything, since
2108 // all incoming packets are considered too old but the buffer will also
2109 // never be flooded and flushed.
2110 packet_buffer_->DiscardAllOldPackets(timestamp_, stats_.get());
2111 }
2112
2113 return rtc::dchecked_cast<int>(extracted_samples);
2114}

2116void NetEqImpl::UpdatePlcComponents(int fs_hz, size_t channels) {
2117 // Delete objects and create new ones.
2118 expand_.reset(expand_factory_->Create(background_noise_.get(),
2119 sync_buffer_.get(), &random_vector_,
2120 stats_.get(), fs_hz, channels));
2121 merge_.reset(new Merge(fs_hz, channels, expand_.get(), sync_buffer_.get()));
2122}
2123
2124void NetEqImpl::SetSampleRateAndChannels(int fs_hz, size_t channels) {
2125 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "SetSampleRateAndChannels " << fs_hz << " "
2126 << channels;
2127 // TODO(hlundin): Change to an enumerator and skip assert.
2128 assert(fs_hz == 8000 || fs_hz == 16000 || fs_hz == 32000 || fs_hz == 48000);
2129 assert(channels > 0);
2130
2131 // Before changing the sample rate, end and report any ongoing expand event.
2132 stats_->EndExpandEvent(fs_hz_);
2133 fs_hz_ = fs_hz;
2134 fs_mult_ = fs_hz / 8000;
2135 output_size_samples_ = static_cast<size_t>(kOutputSizeMs * 8 * fs_mult_);
2136 decoder_frame_length_ = 3 * output_size_samples_; // Initialize to 30ms.
2137
2138 last_mode_ = Mode::kNormal;
2139
2140 ComfortNoiseDecoder* cng_decoder = decoder_database_->GetActiveCngDecoder();
2141 if (cng_decoder)
2142 cng_decoder->Reset();
2143
2144 // Reinit post-decode VAD with new sample rate.
2145 assert(vad_.get()); // Cannot be NULL here.
2146 vad_->Init();
2147
2148 // Delete algorithm buffer and create a new one.
2149 algorithm_buffer_.reset(new AudioMultiVector(channels));
2150
2151 // Delete sync buffer and create a new one.
2152 sync_buffer_.reset(new SyncBuffer(channels, kSyncBufferSize * fs_mult_));
2153
2154 // Delete BackgroundNoise object and create a new one.
2155 background_noise_.reset(new BackgroundNoise(channels));
2156
2157 // Reset random vector.
2158 random_vector_.Reset();
2159
2160 UpdatePlcComponents(fs_hz, channels);
2161
2162 // Move index so that we create a small set of future samples (all 0).
2163 sync_buffer_->set_next_index(sync_buffer_->next_index() -
2164 expand_->overlap_length());
2165
2166 normal_.reset(new Normal(fs_hz, decoder_database_.get(), *background_noise_,
2167 expand_.get(), stats_.get()));
2168 accelerate_.reset(
2169 accelerate_factory_->Create(fs_hz, channels, *background_noise_));
2170 preemptive_expand_.reset(preemptive_expand_factory_->Create(
2171 fs_hz, channels, *background_noise_, expand_->overlap_length()));
2172
2173 // Delete ComfortNoise object and create a new one.
2174 comfort_noise_.reset(
2175 new ComfortNoise(fs_hz, decoder_database_.get(), sync_buffer_.get()));
2176
2177 // Verify that |decoded_buffer_| is long enough.
2178 if (decoded_buffer_length_ < kMaxFrameSize * channels) {
2179 // Reallocate to larger size.
2180 decoded_buffer_length_ = kMaxFrameSize * channels;
2181 decoded_buffer_.reset(new int16_t[decoded_buffer_length_]);
2182 }
2183 RTC_CHECK(controller_) << "Unexpectedly found no NetEqController";
2184 controller_->SetSampleRate(fs_hz_, output_size_samples_);
2185}
2186
2187NetEqImpl::OutputType NetEqImpl::LastOutputType() {
2188 assert(vad_.get());
2189 assert(expand_.get());
2190 if (last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecInternalCng ||
2191 last_mode_ == Mode::kRfc3389Cng) {
2192 return OutputType::kCNG;
2193 } else if (last_mode_ == Mode::kExpand && expand_->MuteFactor(0) == 0) {
2194 // Expand mode has faded down to background noise only (very long expand).
2195 return OutputType::kPLCCNG;
2196 } else if (last_mode_ == Mode::kExpand) {
2197 return OutputType::kPLC;
2198 } else if (vad_->running() && !vad_->active_speech()) {
2199 return OutputType::kVadPassive;
2200 } else if (last_mode_ == Mode::kCodecPlc) {
2201 return OutputType::kCodecPLC;
2202 } else {
2203 return OutputType::kNormalSpeech;
2204 }
